caption: I LOVED the service, however the main meals were lacking in flavor. If you go Make sure to try the carrot cake-it’s amazing! Will be going back to try different dishes.

This place is just amazing. I may have already written a review of them in the past, but this food belongs in a city 10 times this big. The Moscow food scene is an episode of the twilight zone anyway but Lodgepole has amazed people who are indifferent to sustenance itself. Outstanding meals and drinks! And our waiter is a Sommelier.

Definitely worth a stop if you are in or passing through Moscow. I have been passing through twice a week for the past 2 months from spokane to Lewiston, and was getting tired of eating the quick fast food options. Finally I had the foresight to look for a healthier alternative and planned my drive home meal ahead.  I was certainly pleased with the result. i had the beat salad with Madagascarian pink peppercorn vinaigrette and the ahi tuna stuffed peppers with humus. Can't wait for my next trip.

Excellent food and service. Well worth the price. Probably the best food I’ve had eating out in a long time. Our server was so knowledgeable and suggested great pairings for my pork chop and my husband’s steak. You can tell quality is a bad of honor for everyone who works here. Easily one of our new favorite spots in Moscow.

First time ever eating here was in Valentine's day and holy moly was it delicious. I was trying food I never thought I'd like but the flavors were all so delicitaly chosen to go together it would of been a crime against science to not think it was absolutely delicious. Shout out to the incredible cooking staff in the back and the kind gentleman that wooed us with his knowledge of fine dining. Can't wait to go back! Thanks for an unforgettable experience!

An absolutely excellent night out. Their 5 course meal is KILLER and the wine pairing takes it to a whole new level. Super knowledgeable and super friendly staff. Can't wait to come back for the next special occasion.

I was really excited to go to Lodgepole with their great reviews and high quality food. We drove over a half hour to try the highly anticipated meal. I was really disappointed. My son and i had bite size steak, which was dry and chewy. The portion size was maybe 6 ounces. The carrots were dry as well. They had great flavor but were small, thin, and lacked succulence. The mashed potatoes were tasty but too thick. We had reservations and no other customers, however, our food took over 30 to arrive to out table. Our guest had a burger and fries. The burger was small, dry, but taste was good. The fries were crisp inside and out. Our bill was $82+ and not worth even half the price. We dine at many high end restaurants. If the food is quality, i dont mind paying the higher price. You get what you pay for! McDonalds and especially  Humble Burger have better burgers and fries without a doubt. Bojacks at Lewiston has higher quality bite size steak which makes Lodgepole feel like a half attempt at a home cooked average meal, not higher end or higher quality. My son and i both ended the evening with stomach issues that were so unpleasant i dare not detail it in my review...multiple bathroom  visits!!!! Save your money and go somewhere else.

Update***01/26/20 We revisited Lodgepole to celebrate an important event, and our dinner experience almost couldn't have been better.  Michael, the Sommelier, took care of us as soon as we entered. We intended to have more of a European, multi-course meal and the staff was more than happy to accommodate us without rushing.  I was very impressed with our Somm's knowledge of his wine and the generosity and care he provided to make sure it was well paired with our food. The atmosphere was light and the lighting spot on. The only thing I would change is the house's selection of ambient music; it just didn't fit. We definitely plan on going back. 'Moved from three to five stars. Nicely done Lodgepole.  ******* Not bad. Overall, I thought it was over priced for the quality of food you received. The service was good. I can't stress enough how important that is. Its good to go to a place they respect that aspect of the dining experience.  I loved sitting out on the patio. Like most fine restaurants in the Moscow Pullman area, however, their prices have gotten ahead of the the quality of their dishes. I was especially disappointed with the gnocchi. I'm willing to bet, though, another trip might prove me wrong.

I expected a lot less than what I got. It looked too expensive and too trendy. Everything was immaculate and designed beautifully. The kitchen is open and you can watch the meal being made. The staff is actually very young considering the level of food and dining experience delivered. The meal was amazing. I ordered steak bites for and appetizer and the steak appetizer was better than most places serve as a primary meal! It was actually almost the same size of steaks I have recieved with full meals at other restaurants. Did I mention the perfectly seasoned garlic mashed potatoes heaped along side of it? The entree came out and our silverware was switched out completely. Perfect service. One meal was vegan and the same attention to detail was put in as though it was not a special order, but a meal regularly prepared in this fashion. My meal was chicken and potatoes with brussel sprouts. The chicken was seasoned and cooked perfectly, and the brussel sprouts, let's just say you could get your kids to fall in love with them here! Silverware was swapped out again and we had dessert. The desert was overly flavored with a syrup but still tasty. Dinner for the evening came out to about half of what I have paid elsewhere for the same experience. Amazing. The only downside, is there are plenty of patrons for the bar, which was 10 feet away from 1/3 of the tables. It was entertaining, but nobody wants to be at this fine of an establishment and have to deal with 50yr old men hitting on college girls that are too drunk.

The “savory toast” as a starter was good. The “seasonal” salad that includes kale, labneh, beets & pumpkin seeds was great! The “rigatoni”, “grilled steak sandwich” and “lodgepole burger” were all tasty and delicious. It is a cozy place with a good service and a friendly staff. And lastly, It is another gratuity-free restaurant in Moscow area, so no need to tip!

For our belated 4th Wedding Anniversary celebration dinner last night (10.27.18), we were downright delighted with this restaurant and food experience! 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟  We started out with a celebratory bottle of 2015 L'Ecole No 41 Cabernet Sauvignon - going back to where “us” started. Then we ordered the Hama Hama Happy Hour clams along with the Roasted Brussels Sprouts for appetizers. The brussel sprouts were to die for!  We both had our eyes on and ordered the Butter Basted Rib-eye. Oh my Lordy!!!! That rib-eye was probably the most tender, properly medium rare, and perfectly seasoned/salted steak and beautifully presented with a slightly crunchy char. The Charred Cumin carrots were lightly seasoned and charred to perfection. The Cougar Gold baked Potato was seasoned and baked to a crispy skin perfection!  We were also sweetly treated to a complimentary desert - a Browned Butter “something” cake, which we both warned our gracious waiter we would probably only be able to eat two bites. He insisted... saying we wouldn’t be disappointed... he was spot on! We both scraped that plate clean! Tangy plum sauce with a bread-pudding like cake topped with the creamiest vanilla ice cream and nut crumble, garnished with fresh sweet apple slices. 🤤😋  The restaurant itself is small and cozy. Wait staff are personable, helpful, team oriented and never stop moving, table chat always short, direct, helpful and sweet - making those that were IN the restaurant were served in a timely manner and service/table/dishes were attended to quickly - no hands were ever empty even if it was another wait staff walking by your table and removing dishes.  And to counter the low star reviews concerning the staff not answering the phone for reservations (suggested)...  it’s true. I heard the phone ring several times, but everyone was extremely busy! Cause when you are actually seated in the restaurant... your experience while there is their #1 priority. The way it should be. 🏆 Leave a message, or call again to follow up. Or just show up (not at peak hours). We personally didn’t have a reservation, and walked in about 5:15pm on a Saturday night. We were quickly and initially seated at the bar, then were offered and moved shortly after to a table near the pass.  We are throughly impressed, and have to say we were very disappointed that we only had $3.00 cash on hand, and couldn’t tip more - because this restaurant is 100% gratuity-free and there was absolutely no option to add a tip without providing cash.  So if you go, bring cash for their pooled tip bucket - it’s a team effort throughout.  And a big shout out to our waiter, Tanner! Thank you! You helped make our anniversary dinner truly a memorable experience! 💞

Had an excellent Ribeye steak and an good meal experience, finished off with special ICECREAM dessert.  Very taste! Service was excellent and attentive. Saw a clam and mussel dish that was devoured! I never rate 5 stars on my first visit. This place actually gets 4 1/2 Stars! Rustic but clean brick inside for back wall, but clean and attractive upscale place and food. Menu eklective (sp) and interesting.  The menu states that TIPS are not needed...but I did it anyway! $$ level of price for good tastie food.  We would bring people here for dinner...Local Pullman places looked ok, but the small town layout of Moscow, ID looked great vs the whindy, run-down look of Washington's town. Makes a difference in your eating experience....  Oh, the special hand crafted lemonade was unusual but excellent in a very Tart&Sweet flavor.  Each one made with Fresh Lemon and probably a simple syrup, poured directly and mixed in the glass each time...refreshing! Thank you Lodgepole for a great experience!

I was thoroughly impressed with this restaurant across the board. Better than the far more prestigious restaurants I've visited in San Diego, Chicago and Honolulu. Definitely recommend Lodgepole to anyone in the Moscow area, as it's the best food around!

The food and atmosphere is AMAZING! The staff is friendly and very professional, and the high quality; local ingredients make the entrees superb.This is by far my favorite restaurant to go to for any special occasion.

The food was an amazing change of pace. Fresh and locally sourced ingredients made everything we ordered special and it tasted great. Our server was very kind and going for lunch was the perfect option as it wasn't crowded. My girlfriend and I will be coming back to work through their seasonal menu.

Wow. That's all I can say. Some of the best service I have ever had, an amazing and friendly atmosphere, and a very well done and thoughtfully prepared menu. One of my favorite restaurants in the Palouse hands down!

This restaurant never disappoints me. The first time i went here was last April on a date with my husband. I just got back from a somewhat extravagant weekend in Seattle eating and drinking at some pretty amazing places. When i sat down to eat I felt like I was right back in Seattle. The environment and design of the restaurant is exactly what Moscow needed. I love the champagne cocktails, the variety of food, that ferdinand ice cream cake is to die for, and those oysters are incredible. My favorite in all of the Palouse hands down (I've lived here for 10 years).
Oysters, please.  And gnocchi.  Can you fry a few of my oysters after I eat a half dozen raw and then add them to my gnocchi?  Also, double the portion.  Thanks.  I'll be in soon.
Very good food, I had the bread bowl, and the lady had the Gnocchi. Both were very good. Portions were on the smaller side but still enough to satisfy.
Great food, cozy and friendly

This is our new favorite date night restaurant. We recently moved back to this area and absolutely fell in love with Lodgepole. The food and service are high quality. The open kitchen atmosphere is marvelous and totally enhances the dining experience, you forget you're in a small college town in northern Idaho. It definitely has big city sophistication without the pretentiousness. I highly recommend.
Eh, it was okay, I wouldn't give it a 5 star. You can tell they try to use good food but taste for us was quite bland.
Very good, but expensive.

My husband and I came here for our anniversary and had the five course meal, and it was phenomenon. The good was the best in town and the service was excellent. They made a special day even more special. Highly recommended.

I have been to amazing restaurants all over the world from LA to Venice, Italy and Bangkok to Sao Paulo. Lodgepole is one of the most amazing restaurants I have ever been to. The chef and his staff really care about the food and the customer and it shows. The presentation, the open kitchen atmosphere, the taste, and the service, is all top tier. With a rotating seasonal menu it stays fresh all year and never gets boring. I highly recommend this diamond in the middle of Idaho to anyone who has the chance to go. The food is just fabulous. Oh.... and the desserts.... don't even get me started.
Incredible chicken and waffles at the weekend. Wonderful specials and consistently excellent service.

This restaurant was an experience! The owner is also the head cook. He knows how to rest a steak properly, best one I've ever had. The appetizers were all amazing, especially the cheese and bread board with the honey... so good! The desert chef really knows what she's doing, and made the best tart and creme brulee. Mmmm. They are also great at pairing wines, which should really make them eligible for more than 5 stars.
Amazing food and staff!  Keep up the great work!
Fabulous food. The green beans were exceptional. The desert was magnificent and service was extremely friendly. Would go there again in a heartbeat
Food was fine but the worst wait of my life it took 20 minutes to get a coke and the seats are so uncomfortable and hard to sit in because of the shiny smooth wood benches make it slidey.

They lost our reservation on Graduation eve, but got us in.  But we were clearly rushed through the service to do so. The food varied from average to superb.  The halibut special  (seared, not so special) was served on a bed of Cold Asparagus and Lentils. Cold.  Meh. The ribeye was perfectly cooked and the pan-seared carrots superb. But ribeyes always leave a pile of fat and trimmings waste that simply don't happen with a NY Strip.  The crab cake appetizer was as good as any I've ever had. The wine and prosecco cocktails were excellent, and the wine list was that rare combination of well-considered and reasonably priced.  Overall, Lodgepole is a good restaurant with occasional flashes of greatness, and occasional lapses.
It's ok just had beer but they had a nice staff
Steak is amazing and service is great. They actually messed up our steak once and they remade it and took it off the bill ($30 entry). Burger is also fantastic. One of best I've ever had.
Valentine's dinner was a rip off. It was advertised as $70 for a fixed price menu but they charged closer to $80 per person. Not impressed.
The best food in Moscow by far!

We have had the opportunity to dine here twice in two weeks visiting our daughter in college. My husband travels a great deal and we love to cook at home so we're pretty picky.  This restaurant from reservation, service to meal is fabulous.  Highly recommend!
Awesome food and atmosphere!  I had the burger and hubby had the steak.  Best steak we've had in a long time.  The rib-eye was so tender.
